.TH "notify_remote_via_irq" 9 "notify_remote_via_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
notify_remote_via_irq \- send event to remote end of event channel via irq
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" notify_remote_via_irq
.BI "(int irq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "irq" 12
irq of event channel to send event to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Unlike \fBnotify_remote_via_evtchn\fP, this is safe to use across
save/restore. Notifications on a broken connection are silently
dropped.
